cs.ET, cs.AR, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.ET (Emerging Technologies): Stochastic computing is an emerging computing technique, which is the focus of this paper. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture): The proposed inner product design is a hardware architecture for stochastic computing. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The scalability of the proposed design is discussed, which relates to distributed and parallel computing. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The sequential processing approach used in the proposed design is related to data structures and algorithms. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The fault tolerance aspect of the proposed design relates to systems and control.
